UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304387801001407
KW  - Gains from trade
KW  - Distribution
KW  - Economic growth
AB  - The paper examines the welfare gains from North–South trade and their distribution. We construct an endogenous growth North–South model with four Southern stages of development as possible equilibria: specialisation in a traditional good; the South, in addition, copies Northern high-tech manufactured goods; the South begins to innovate in its own right; and finally, a stage in which the South only innovates, as in the North. We use this model to show that dynamic gains from trade and from Southern development through the stages can create new winners, unskilled workers in the North, and skilled workers in the South.
